JsonHandler - Class in data
The JsonHandler class provides utility methods to serialize Java objects to JSON format and deserialize JSON strings back to Java objects using the Jackson library's ObjectMapper.
JsonHandler() - Constructor for class data.JsonHandler
Creates a new JsonHandler with a default ObjectMapper instance.
jsonToObject(String, Class<T>) - Method in class data.JsonHandler
Deserializes a JSON string to a Java object of the specified class.
